# Mock Figma System

This project has a mock Figma system for workshop participants without Figma access.

## Two Skills

1. **`mock-figma-implement-design`** — Implement a component from pre-recorded mock data (no Figma MCP needed). Read the skill at `.claude/skills/mock-figma-implement-design/SKILL.md`.
2. **`record-mock-figma`** — Record new mock data from a live Figma file. Read the skill at `.claude/skills/record-mock-figma/SKILL.md`.

## Quick Reference

- Mock data lives in `mock-figma-data/`
- Registry at `mock-figma-data/registry.json` maps keywords and URLs to mock entries
- Each mock has a `response.json` (design context), `screenshot.png`, and `assets/` folder
- Available keywords: check `registry.json` → `mocks` keys

## When to Use

- User says "mock figma" or "mock-figma-implement-design" → use `mock-figma-implement-design` skill
- User says "record mock" or "record-mock-figma" → use `record-mock-figma` skill
- User provides a Figma URL and Figma MCP is not available → check if URL exists in `registry.json` → `urlToKeyword`, then use mock
